GN is $\\sim$33%. We develop a new method to measure the\nintrinsic line-of-sight column density distribution of AGN in the nearby\nuniverse, which we find the result is in good agreement with the constraints\nfrom recent population synthesis models.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 7 Nov 2020 21:22:57 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 10 Nov 2020 14:56:38 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 2 Apr 2021 13:57:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-06-09"}
